<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT AXLES: INTERNATIONAL BY SPICER I-BEAM - KING PIN BUSHING REPLACEMENT - KING PIN BUSHING REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>KING PIN BUSHING REMOVAL</title>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>Screw threads MUST be lubricated with high pressure lubricant prior to being used.</para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Select the appropriate service tool kit (pilots, remover and installer) for axle code
                number. All axles incorporate pre-sized bushings. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02004t_13.xml" xrefid="hl0200401">SPECIAL TOOLS</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure knuckle in a vise using brass jaws. Assemble screw, support plate and remover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200410">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200410" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200410" filename="../figg02/G0200410.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Bushing Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SCREW ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SUPPORT PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. OLD BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. REMOVER/INSTALLER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten screw with wrench until bushing is removed from knuckle.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove knuckle from vise. Secure opposite end of knuckle. Assemble tool at opposite end to
                remove remaining bushing.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
